South African Government Proposes to Take Over Rail Planning From Transnet

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-08-25T10:23:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/south-african-government-proposes-to-take-over-rail-planning-from-transnet.html
South Africa ’s government is
considering taking over the management of the country’s rail
assets from Transnet SOC Ltd., Brian Molefe, chief executive
officer of the state-owned rail and ports company, said.  Transnet and the government is discussing the proposal,
which was made by the Department of Transport, Molefe told
reporters in Johannesburg today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
